4.2.2 Text Input and Form Entry
If a platform, app, or website includes a user interface that requires text input or form entry, accommodations must be made to prevent these tasks from becoming repetitive.

4.2.2-A
All 10-foot platforms, apps, and websites that offer manual keyboard entry via a physical remote for user interfaces like account authentication, search, etc. must allow keyboard entry from a mobile app.

4.2.2-B
When a platform, app, or website requires more complex form entry, like address or credit card input, the user flow must include options to copy or save form content to eliminate repetitive form interactions.

4.2.2-C
All platforms, apps, and websites that require form input must offer autocompletion controls.
